FBIS4-43041 "drweu113_g_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-113 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 CANADA Government To Suspend Commercial Flights to Haiti Government To Suspend Commercial Flights to Haiti PA1006190294 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1744 GMT 10 Jun 94 PA1006190294 Mexico City NOTIMEX Spanish BFN [Text] Montreal, 10 Jun (NOTIMEX) -- The Canadian Government will suspend commercial flights to Haiti beginning on 25 June, Andre Ouellet, the Canadian minister of foreign affairs, has announced. He added that the decision to suspend commercial flights to Haiti was made to comply with a resolution that the OAS adopted last week calling for increased pressure on the coupist Haitian Government. Ouellet said that he plans to discuss with the cabinet the adoption of "additional measures," which according to official sources, "will affect the financial transactions" between the two countries. The United States today announced the suspension of flights to Haiti, beginning on 25 June. The Canadian Foreign Affairs Ministry also recommended to its citizens in that country to "leave the island while possible through regular flights."
